{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b0549f77-62e4-45b9-9586-7d26e61ab315","content":"TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform with its own **treenode-filter** syntax. The filter path format is `/{assembly}/{namespace}/{class}/{test}`.\n\nTo run only `SmsNotificationTests`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests\"\n```\n\nThe wildcards `*` match any assembly and namespace, then `SmsNotificationTests` matches the class. This will run both `SendSms_HealthCheck` and `SendSms_ValidPhone_Succeeds`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9fc4a37e-4072-40a4-890b-06863d4de9c9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"This is a TUnit project. TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) natively. For TUnit, the filter syntax is different from VSTest. Let me check how to filter by class in TUnit.\n\nTUnit uses its own treenode-filter syntax. To filter by class name, the syntax is:\n\n```\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests\"\n```\n\nOr with the MTP filter:\n\n```\ndotnet run -- --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests\"\n```\n\nWait, actually TUnit 0.6.x uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform. The filter syntax for TUnit uses `--treenode-filter`. The treenode filter pattern is `/{assembly}/{namespace}/{class}/{test}`.\n\n\nSo to filter by class, I'd use `--treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests\"`, but with `dotnet test` I might need to pass it through to MTP properly, either directly or via `--filter` with the appropriate syntax.\n\nActually, let me reconsider this. TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform, so with `dotnet test` and MTP, I can use `--treenode-filter` directly since the treenode path format follows `/{assembly}/{namespace}/{class}/{test}`. The command would be `dotnet test --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests\"`, or if running directly, `dotnet run -- --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests\"`.","outputTokens":547,"requestId":"9C42:1554C1:1746155:19FACCC:69F864D8"},"id":"f3e1311f-9ee3-41f8-a342-b7867a037b1c","timestamp":"2026-05-04T09:20:35.551Z","parentId":"e58beddf-a588-4e11-8691-beea5505e863"}
